@Rabi i have not heard of any plans to get rid of neutron from Undercloud atleast in Zed release. But as you mentioned previously @Dan may be aware about the past work and future plans about this, i have missed reach out to him that time @Dan can you please provide any details about the plan.

wrt driver of https://review.opendev.org/850158 change, is getting rid of ml2 ovs completely by default so that it can be deprecated/removed in future patches, overcloud already default to ovn, and that change switches default for Undercloud too.

wrt value the idea is to not allow upgrade if ml2 plugin change is detected whenever Neutron is deployed as that can break Undercloud as it also requires migration of network resources(Migration is not evaluated yet for Undercloud). This check can be cleaned up whenever neutron is dropped from Undercloud or follow up release of deprecation/removal of ml2 ovs. So yes if Neutron is dropped from Undercloud this change will not be any value.

